# Yso systems (Ysindrolir)

## Scope

Achaea **Yso** automation under `Ysindrolir/`. **Supported combat classes:** Magi and Alchemist (shared Yso core). Do not reintroduce removed stacks (e.g. Occultist routes); strip obsolete empty Mudlet folders/triggers from `Yso system.xml` when editing that package.

## Canonical Lua vs Mudlet package

- Prefer editing Lua **on disk**, then re-embed into `Ysindrolir/mudlet packages/Yso system.xml` via **`Ysindrolir/scripts/export_yso_system_xml.ps1`** (`cd Ysindrolir\scripts` then run the script).
- New or renamed Mudlet **Script** bodies must be listed in that script’s **`$ScriptToSourcePath`** hashtable (Mudlet `<name>` → repo path). After manifest changes, run the export script.
- Validate XML after export: `[xml](Get-Content -Raw -LiteralPath '...\mudlet packages\Yso system.xml')` in PowerShell.

## Api / curing skeleton

- Canonical file: **`Ysindrolir/Yso/Core/api.lua`** (Mudlet script name **`Api stuff`**).
- Keep **`Ysindrolir/Yso/xml/api_stuff.lua`** identical to `Core/api.lua` (bootstrap may `require("Yso.xml.api_stuff")` as fallback to `Yso.Core.api`).

## Bootstrap / routes

- **`Ysindrolir/Yso/xml/yso_bootstrap_loader.lua`** and **`Ysindrolir/Yso/xml/route_chassis_loader.lua`**: keep **Alchemist / Magi** `pcall(require, …)` blocks **in the same order**. New class modules: register in **`Ysindrolir/Yso/Combat/route_registry.lua`** and extend both loaders per the checklist comments there.

## Reference data

- Affliction/cure metadata: **`Ysindrolir/Information/AFFLICTION_CURES.txt`**. Header and usage should reflect **supported classes** (e.g. Magi, Alchemist), not removed ones.

## Removed tooling

- **`YsoDevtools.xml`** was removed from the repo; do not add it back. Queue/debug helpers live under generic **`Yso`** APIs and README-documented aliases only.

## Queue / lanes

- **`Ysindrolir/Yso/Core/queue.lua`**: entity-lane inference uses carve-outs for certain `command …` patterns; preserve behaviour unless gameplay rules change—document rationale in comments when adjusting.
